dcterms:description: The CIFAR-10 dataset consists of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in computer vision.

dcterms:description: The ImageNet dataset is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains over 14 million images, categorized into over 20,000 categories.
